Prague transport company delivers chip card for first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 is the date in the history of the Prague Transport Company when the first passenger boards subways, trams and buses with an electronic coupon in his pocket instead of a paper line ticket.
The coupon is currently available to around 100,000 people who have an Opencard chip card.
Passengers can purchase 30-day, 90-day and annual coupons (valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time save on their chip cards in the information centers and branches of the Transport Company at the Muzeum, M<0xC5><0xAF>stek, Nádra<0xC5><0xBE>í Hole<0xC5><0xA1>ovice, And<0xC4><0x9B>l, Roztyly, Let<0xC5><0x88>any, Kobylisy, Rajská zra.
The coupons can be purchased online from yesterday via the website of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
The service was used by more than 400 customers until the afternoon.
Those who start using the internet can finally forget the publishing windows of the metro stations, where until now they had to stand in long lines for line tickets on a regular basis.
The coupon can be purchased online and saved on the Opencard in one of the 13 accounts of the City Library.
“At these locations, passengers have a counter with trained servers to help those interested to shop online and also save their purchased coupons on their card,” said Martin Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD>, the project’s spokesman.
In addition to libraries, electronic coupons can be saved on Opencards in self-service vending machines installed in a few lobbies.
What do these machines look like?
They are red, reminiscent of the ticket managers, and the passengers may have noticed them at the metro stations Roztyly, Bud<0xC4><0x9B>jovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"There are currently five of them in the city, but it should be eighty by the end of the year," Opatrn<0xC3><0xBD> added.
The coupon is checked by an automatic instead of the driver
Automated machines starting tomorrow are easy to operate.
Simply insert the Opencard chip card and the previously paid coupon will be saved on its own.
From tomorrow, electronic coupons will be valid not only in the capital, but also in the surrounding area.
So, on trains and bus lines around the city from 300 to 499, which are mainly used by residents of the districts of central Bohemia to travel to the capital.
