Recently, the opening to the North (i.e. the area beginning at the 49th parallel) was frequently featured in the Prime Minister’s speeches, but he has never given a lecture on this subject.
The head of state, however, merely explained why he considered the North to be a “treasure mine full of enormous potential”, but he did not mention the time factor, investment amounts or specific priorities for future projects.
