This area, which is "twice the size of France", is "the territory of our territory, Quebec."
It is found not only in us, but also in us,” the head of state reiterated, stressing that he intends to create a national founding myth.
He pointed out that Quebec's development was largely determined by its relationship with the North: the gold rush in Abitibi, Quebec's design work, James Bay...
"This is ours, our future," he added, after taking a theatrical break from looking at the huge map behind him.
